"{\"uid\": \"tribune.com.pk-story-2483621-goofy-girl-titmus-struggling-to-believe-olympic-gold\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"US The 23-year-old beat McIntosh and Ledecky to win her second consecutive Olympic 400m freestyle title Ariarne Titmus said Saturday she can not believe \\\"a goofy girl\\\" from Australia could win back-to-back Olympic 400m freestyle titles, while lavishing praise on rival Katie Ledecky.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 2, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9481065111736438, \"rank\": 0.02889967614158656, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 25, \"end\": 33, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998903632721654, \"rank\": 9.831145305897582e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 37, \"to\": 44}, {\"ngram\": \"her second consecutive Olympic 400m freestyle title\", \"from\": 52, \"to\": 103}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"a goofy girl\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 166}, {\"ngram\": \"back\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 205}, {\"ngram\": \"praise\", \"from\": 253, \"to\": 259}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The down-to-earth 23-year-old held off Canadian teenager Summer McIntosh and American great Ledecky to join Dawn Fraser as the only Australian female swimmer to retain an Olympic crown.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 364, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999767574538432, \"rank\": 1.770443496059632e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 395, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Fraser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dawn Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Fraser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Fraser\"}, {\"begin\": 419, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9958362578732088, \"rank\": 0.004176391336946242, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"earth\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 304}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic crown\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world record holder was in full control to touch in 3mins 57.49secs ahead of McIntosh (3:58.37) and Ledecky (4:00.86), who faded badly in the final 50m.\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world record holder\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 497}, {\"ngram\": \"full control\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"McIntosh\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 563}, {\"ngram\": \"3:58.37\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 572}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"4:00.86\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 594}, {\"ngram\": \"the final 50m.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not believe that's me, to be honest,\\\" she said when asked about what the feat meant.\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 723, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the feat\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I look at myself and I am so normal.\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I love swimming, and I love getting out and representing my country and having fun.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"my country\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"fun\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope nobody looks at me any differently.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just the same old goofy Tassie (Tasmanian) girl out here living out her dream.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just the same old goofy Tassie (Tasmanian) girl\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"her dream\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 974}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope it goes to show, anyone can do what they want to do if they work hard and believe in themselves.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1008}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And here I am, from little old Launie (Launceston), a town of 90,000, and I am out here living the dream.\\\"\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Launceston_Football_Club\", \"score\": 0.9999997517109331, \"rank\": 2.4445477822623113e-07, \"text\": \"Launceston\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Launceston_Football_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Launceston_Football_Club\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"little old Launie\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"a town\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"the dream\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus, who dethroned Ledecky in Tokyo, came to France in red-hot form after shattering the 200m world record and swimming the second-quickest 400m ever at the Australian trials.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1190, \"end\": 1196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1223, \"end\": 1228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9552843376085127, \"rank\": 0.0468087402687579, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9221684340468734, \"rank\": 0.08257551616341204, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9958362578732088, \"rank\": 0.004176391336946242, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"red-hot form\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m world record\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Ledecky can never be written off and McIntosh was always going to be a threat after snatching Titmus's world record last year before the Australian took it back.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1511, \"end\": 1521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9958362578732088, \"rank\": 0.004176391336946242, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"a threat\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it was all Titmus in Paris, who was near world record pace at the halfway mark and comfortably surged home, with McIntosh winning her first Olympic medal by taking silver.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999952475265, \"rank\": 4.75247366437345e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1659, \"end\": 1667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"world record pace\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"the halfway mark\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"her first Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just happy to get the result for myself, and I am so honoured to be part of the race and be alongside legends like Katie,\\\" Titmus said.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1848, \"end\": 1854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1797}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1809}, {\"ngram\": \"legends\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1834}, {\"ngram\": \"Katie\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I look up to her so much as an athlete, and it is certainly not a rivalry beyond the races.\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"a rivalry\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"the races\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I really respect her as a person.\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1988, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her longevity in the sport.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her longevity\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2002}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's nice to catch up and have a chat.\\\"\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a chat\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's fun racing the best in the world,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It gets the best out of me; it gets the best out of them.\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2168, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really hope all the hype lived up to the expectation.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the hype\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2195}, {\"ngram\": \"the expectation\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I really hope that I put on a good show tonight and everyone enjoyed it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good show\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2264}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus will also swim the 200m and 800m in Paris.\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999952475265, \"rank\": 4.75247366437345e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 200m\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky has opted out of the shorter distance, focusing instead on defending her 800m and 1500m titles.\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2358}, {\"ngram\": \"the shorter distance\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2396}, {\"ngram\": \"her 800m\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2436}, {\"ngram\": \"1500m titles\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh is also skipping the 200m free, instead prioritising the 200m and 400m medley and 200m butterfly.\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 200m\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2526}]}, {\"sentence\": \"COMMENT